# Type identity and coercion

`TypeEnvironment` and `TypeId` own semantics.

## Contract

- Input: parsed type references, declaration shells and AST context
- Output: canonical `TypeId`s and contextual coercion rules
- Decides: semantic type identity, collection/map shapes, contextual compatibility
- Must not decide: access modes, runtime ownership, backend lowering
- Invariant: `TypeId` equality in the active `TypeEnvironment` is the only semantic comparison rule

## Main paths

- `src/compiler_frontend/datatypes/`
- `src/compiler_frontend/type_coercion/`
- `src/compiler_frontend/value_mode.rs`
- `src/compiler_frontend/ast/type_resolution/`

